description:
Credential management UI: list, issue, revoke JWT credentials for a tenant. Builds on H1 (tenant/database picker), C1 (tenant-admin authz), and C3 (credential control-plane endpoints).

## Scope

### 1. New route: ui/src/routes/credentials/+page.svelte

A new top-level page at /credentials that:

- Shows the current tenant (from getSelectedTenant())
- Lists existing credentials for that tenant (via GET /control/tenants/:id/credentials)
- Has an "Issue Credential" button that opens a modal
- Per-row revoke button

### 2. Credential listing

Table columns: jti (truncated), target user_id (truncated), issued_at, expires_at, grants summary, revoked flag, actions (Revoke button for non-revoked rows).

Use a shared formatters util if it exists (e.g. ui/src/lib/format.ts) or inline Date(iss*1000).toISOString() formatting.

### 3. Issue Credential modal

Fields:
- Target user (text input for UserId UUID)
- TTL seconds (number input, default 3600 = 1 hour)
- Grants builder:
  - Add a database row
  - Per-database: name (text) + ops checkbox group {Read, Write, Admin}
  - Multiple databases allowed

On submit:
- POST /control/tenants/:id/credentials with body { target_user, ttl_seconds, grants: { databases: [...] } }
- On 200/201: show a one-time dialog with the signed JWT. The JWT is returned ONCE and never again retrievable. Include a "Copy to Clipboard" button. After closing, the dialog's JWT value is wiped.
- On 403: show the error.code ("grants_exceed_role" etc.) in a friendly message.
- On other errors: show the server error detail.

### 4. Revoke confirmation

On clicking Revoke: show a confirm dialog. On confirm, DELETE /control/tenants/:id/credentials/:jti. On success, refresh the list (the revoked credential should either disappear or show a "revoked" flag).

### 5. API helpers in ui/src/lib/api.ts

Add these exports:

    export type Credential = {
      jti: string;
      user_id: string;
      tenant_id: string;
      issued_at_ms: number;
      expires_at_ms: number;
      revoked: boolean;
      grants: Grants;
    };

    export type Grants = {
      databases: GrantedDatabase[];
    };

    export type GrantedDatabase = {
      name: string;
      ops: Array<"read" | "write" | "admin">;
    };

    export type IssueCredentialRequest = {
      target_user: string;
      ttl_seconds: number;
      grants: Grants;
    };

    export type IssueCredentialResponse = {
      jwt: string;
      jti: string;
      expires_at_ms: number;
    };

    export async function listCredentials(tenantId: string): Promise<Credential[]> {
      const response = await request<{ credentials: Credential[] }>(
        `/control/tenants/${encodeURIComponent(tenantId)}/credentials`,
      );
      return response.credentials;
    }

    export async function issueCredential(
      tenantId: string,
      body: IssueCredentialRequest,
    ): Promise<IssueCredentialResponse> {
      return request<IssueCredentialResponse>(
        `/control/tenants/${encodeURIComponent(tenantId)}/credentials`,
        { method: "POST", body: JSON.stringify(body) },
      );
    }

    export async function revokeCredential(
      tenantId: string,
      jti: string,
    ): Promise<void> {
      await request<void>(
        `/control/tenants/${encodeURIComponent(tenantId)}/credentials/${encodeURIComponent(jti)}`,
        { method: "DELETE" },
      );
    }

These are control-plane calls so they do NOT pass a scope.

### 6. Navigation link

Add a /credentials link to the main navigation (wherever the existing tenant/schemas/collections/audit links live — probably ui/src/routes/+layout.svelte or a nav component).

### 7. Tests

bun test in ui/:
- ui/src/lib/api.test.ts — extend with tests for listCredentials, issueCredential, revokeCredential URL building.
- Component tests are optional for this bead; the primary verification is the type check + svelte-check + manual visual inspection.

svelte-check:
- bun run check (or npm run check) must pass after all the new Svelte files land.

## Out of scope

- Login / JWT storage / authenticated SDK session — H2 assumes the existing dev-mode auth or --no-auth; a full login flow is a separate bead.
- Self-issue vs admin-issue distinction at UI level — the server enforces this; the UI just posts and handles the 403.
- Credential rotation / renewal — no UI for this.
- Audit view showing which credential issued a change — later bead.

## Context

- C3 landed the server-side endpoints at /control/tenants/:id/credentials (POST/GET/DELETE)
- H1 landed the tenant/database picker and the new path-based request helper
- The UI is Svelte 5 with runes
- The Copy-to-Clipboard function should use navigator.clipboard.writeText with a fallback

## Files to touch

- ui/src/lib/api.ts — add Credential types + listCredentials/issueCredential/revokeCredential
- ui/src/routes/credentials/+page.svelte — NEW
- ui/src/routes/+layout.svelte — add nav link (check the existing nav location)
- ui/src/lib/api.test.ts — extend with URL-building tests for the new helpers

## Files NOT to touch

- Any Rust crate
- sdk/typescript/*
- The existing tenant/schemas/collections/audit pages

## Verification

- bun run check (svelte-check) passes
- bun test passes (46 existing + new tests)
- Manual dev server smoke: navigate to /credentials, see the list, try the issue modal (may 401 without a real auth session — that's OK for this bead, the UI should show the error clearly)

